# Use Broadcast Groups for vstd Lemmas

When you need vstd lemmas (arithmetic, sequence properties, etc.), bring them in via `broadcast use` at the top of the `verus!` block rather than calling individual lemmas.

## Correct Pattern

```rust
verus! {

broadcast use vstd::arithmetic::mul::group_mul_properties;

fn my_function(...) {
    // Arithmetic lemmas are now available automatically
}

} // verus!
```

## When to Call Lemmas Directly

Only call specific lemmas directly when:
1. **Instantiation required** — the lemma needs specific arguments to trigger
2. **Performance** — broadcast groups add too much overhead for a simple proof

## Common Broadcast Groups

| Group | Provides |
|-------|----------|
| `vstd::arithmetic::mul::group_mul_properties` | Multiplication commutativity, associativity, distributivity |
| `vstd::arithmetic::div_mod::group_div_properties` | Division properties |
| `vstd::arithmetic::div_mod::group_mod_properties` | Modulo properties |
| `vstd::std_specs::vec::group_vec_axioms` | Vec length, indexing specs |

## Why

- Cleaner code — no scattered lemma calls
- Proof automation — SMT solver can use lemmas as needed
- Maintainability — adding/removing lemmas happens in one place
